title: Helcogramma desa
text: Helcogramma desa, the neglected triplefin, is a species of <a href="triplefin">triplefin</a> blenny in the genus "<a href="Helcogramma">Helcogramma</a>". It was <a href="Species%20description">described</a> by Jeffery T. Williams and Jeffrey C. Howe in 2003. This species is known from the western Pacific in Vietnam and the Philippines, including the <a href="Spratly%20Islands">Spratly Islands</a>.
